      "writtenOn": "2020-11-10T23:34:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Lets hold off on this malloc()-aware reasoning for a follow up?  If we land this these 20 lines or so are going to read bizarrely... why apply kMinHeapAllocCount over here but kMallocRoundUp over here when both sides of the if-statement round up to a minimum count to allocate on the heap using malloc?\n\nIt really seems like we want one or the other but definitely not both of the round-to-something bits for any allocation we do, independent of addExtraSpace.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 558,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 567,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "bd25c98593712f1d51dd5037d8f13018bf87db2d",
