      "writtenOn": "2020-11-11T01:29:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Removed the kMallocRoundUp logic. It\u0027s not something I\u0027ve seen other vector-like classes do anyway. This has the nice side benefit of simplifying the `capacity() \u003d\u003d 15` test back to its original form.\n\nFor now I\u0027ll leave the kMinHeapAllocCount logic as-is (except in kExactFit) but I definitely think it could stand to be improved. It seems to add value when sizeof(T)\u003c\u003d4 or so, but as sizeof(T) grows it eventually becomes a liability.",
      "parentUuid": "c3cf5150_103c7449",
